 Prompt 10 – Review & Retention Message
 
## Version 1 (v10.1)

### Prompt
Ask the customer for a review.

### Change Made
Initial version

### Observed Effect
Low engagement
No emotional connection

### Lesson Learned
Post-engagement requires relationship-focused tone

Respond 

### **Customer Review Request (Professional & Polite)**

Hi [Customer Name],

We hope everything is running smoothly at your café! It’s been great supporting your business with Flexikitch.

If you’ve been happy with your experience, we’d really appreciate it if you could take a moment to share a quick review. Your feedback helps other café owners make confident decisions and allows us to keep improving our service.

It only takes a minute, and it would mean a lot to our team.

**[Insert Review Link]**

Thank you again for choosing Flexikitch — we look forward to continuing to support your growth.

Best regards,
[Your Name]
Flexikitch Team


## Version 2 (v10.2)

### Prompt
You are a customer success manager. Write a message asking a satisfied Flexikitch client for a review. Include appreciation, simple request, and optional referral mention. Keep friendly and under 100 words.

Respond 
Hi [Customer Name],

Thanks so much for choosing Flexikitch—we really appreciate your support and are glad to hear things are going well at your café!

If you have a moment, we’d love it if you could share a quick review of your experience. It helps other café owners feel confident and helps us keep improving.

Also, if you know anyone who could benefit from Flexikitch, feel free to refer them—we’d really appreciate it.

Thanks again!
[Your Name]


### Change Made
Added role (customer success manager)
Included appreciation + request + referral
Added tone + word limit constraints

### Observed Effect
Friendly, natural communication
Higher likelihood of response

### Lesson Learned
Tone + structure improve customer engagement and retention
